{"lemma":"فَحْلٌ","slug":"فَحْلٌ","root":"ف.ح.ل","root_slug":"ف-ح-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ح-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n33147"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%AD%D9%92%D9%84%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"stallion, he-camel"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a vigorous, manly man, who surpasses others"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"male palm-tree"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Canopus"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَحَلَ (faḥala) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to put to the females for breeding"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Inherited from Proto-Semitic *paḥal-. Compare also ف ح ش (f ḥ š)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33147","headword_ar":"فَحْلٌ","root":"fHl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a word of well-known meaning, (S, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A male"},{"kind":"text","text":"of animals (Mgh, Msb, K) of any kind, (Mgh, K,) [including mankind: and particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a stallion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"generally,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a male"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stallion"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA:) pl. [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuHuwlN","text_ar":"فُحُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiHaAlN","text_ar":"فِحَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuHuwlapN","text_ar":"فُحُولَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiHaAlapN","text_ar":"فِحَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K) and [pl. of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoHulN","text_ar":"اَفْحُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faHiylN","text_ar":"فَحِيلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faHolN","text_ar":"فَحْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Kr, TA;) and [particularly]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faHol","text_ar":"فَحْل"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the camels."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA.) ―         -b2-  Hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaHolu","text_ar":"الفَحْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an appellation of (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Canopus"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suhayolN","text_ar":"سُهَيْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"); because it is aloof from the other stars, like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fHl","text_ar":"فحل"},{"kind":"text","text":"which, when he has covered, goes aloof from the [she-] camels: (S, O, K, TA:) or, as some say, it is so called because of its greatness. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faHiylN","text_ar":"فَحِيلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"means the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faHolN","text_ar":"فَحْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A masculine, as opposed to an effeminate, man"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN faHolapN","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ فَحْلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A clamorous"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or, app.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"masculine"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"woman."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuHuwlu Al$~uEaraA='i","text_ar":"فُحُولُ الشُّعَرَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an appellation applied to (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The poets"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who have overcome,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who overcome,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in satirizing, those who have vied with them therein;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K;) like Jereer and El-Farezdak, (O, TA,) who used to be called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faHolaA muDara","text_ar":"فَحْلَا مُضَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and in like manner (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any one who, when he vies with a poet, is judged to have excelled him"},{"kind":"text","text":"[is called a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faHol","text_ar":"فَحْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (K, TA; [for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDala","text_ar":"فَضَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the CK, I read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuD~ila","text_ar":"فُضِّلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in other copies of the K;]) like 'Alkameh Ibn-'Abadeh; (TA;) who was surnamed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaHolu","text_ar":"الفَحْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"because he took to wife Umm-Jundab when Imrael-Keys divorced her on the occasion of her judging him [i. e. 'Alkameh] to have overcome him [Imra-el-Keys] in poetry. (S, O, K, TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faHolN","text_ar":"فَحْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also means [app. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A vigorous orator:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haAdirN","text_ar":"هَادِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b6-  And] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A relater, reciter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rehearser, by heart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of poetry, and of traditions, or narratives learned, or heard, or received, from another or others;] syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAwK","text_ar":"رَاوٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuHuwlN","text_ar":"فُحُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) so in the M. (TA.) ―         -b7-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuH~aAlN","text_ar":"فُحَّالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places. And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutafaH~ilN","text_ar":"مُتَفَحِّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b8-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mat that is made of the woven leaves of the palm-tree thus called,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, * S, * O, * K, * TA,) i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the palm-tree called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuH~aAl","text_ar":"فُحَّال"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, K, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuHuwlN","text_ar":"فُحُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O, TA.) ―         -b9-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rain"},{"kind":"text","text":"is thus called [in a verse of Et-Tirimmáh Ibn-El-Hakeem, being likened to the stallion-camel, because of its fertilizing the earth]. (Ham p. 110.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","Mgh","Msb","K","MA","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}